Distribution.
Metriaclima aurora
is distributed at Likoma Island ( type locality) and along the coast of Mozambique at Mara Point, Mbweca, Tumbi Point, and a relatively isolated location to the south near N’kolongwe (
Fig. 1
). Mbweca and Tumbi Point are the only localities where the brown-barred males are found. Populations have been transplanted to Thumbi West Island, where the species has spread to several locations around Cape Maclear (
Stauffer & Hert 1992
;
Konings 2001
).
